---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Structural Analysis · Virtual Labs · AquinTutor" description="Plane trusses by joints and sections, shear-force and bending-moment diagrams, beam deflection by Macaulay's method, influence lines and Euler column buckling — all computed live.">

<style>
  body { background: #0a0a0c; color: #e8e8ee; margin: 0; }
  .sa-wrap { max-width: 1360px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 24px 4vw 80px; }
  .sa-back { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px; font-family: 'Geist Mono', ui-monospace, monospace; font-size: 11px; color: #9aa0a6; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .sa-back:hover { color: #67e8f9; }
  .sa-eye { font-family: 'Geist Mono', ui-monospace, monospace; font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.18em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #67e8f9; font-weight: 700; }
  .sa-title { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 38px; font-weight: 600; margin: 4px 0 6px; letter-spacing: -0.02em; line-height: 1.1; }
  .sa-title em { color: #67e8f9; font-style: italic; font-weight: 500; }
  .sa-sub { color: #9aa0a6; max-width: 840px; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.55; margin: 0 0 22px; }

  .sa-shell { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 268px minmax(0,1fr); gap: 18px; }
  @media (max-width: 960px) { .sa-shell { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }

  .sa-exp-list { background: #11131a; border: 1px solid #2a2a35; border-radius: 12px; padding: 10px; align-self: start; position: sticky; top: 14px; }
  .sa-exp-list h4 { font-family: 'Geist Mono', ui-monospace, monospace; font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 0.16em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #fbbf24; font-weight: 700; margin: 6px 8px 10px; }
  .sa-exp { display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 9px; width: 100%; text-align: left; background: transparent; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 8px; color: #cfd6da; font-family: inherit; padding: 9px 10px; cursor: pointer; margin-bottom: 2px; }
  .sa-exp:hover { background: #15171f; }
  .sa-exp.active { background: rgba(103,232,249,0.10); border-color: #67e8f9; }
  .sa-exp .num { font-family: 'Geist Mono', ui-monospace, monospace; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; color: #67e8f9; flex: 0 0 auto; width: 18px; }
  .sa-exp .nm { font-size: 12.5px; line-height: 1.3; }
  .sa-exp.active .nm { color: #fff; }

  .sa-bench { min-width: 0; }
  .sa-exp-head { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 26px; font-weight: 600; margin: 0 0 4px; color: #fff; }
  .sa-exp-tag { font-family: 'Geist Mono', ui-monospace, monospace; font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 0.14em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #67e8f9; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 14px; }

  .sa-tabs { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 4px; margin-bottom: 18px; border-bottom: 1px solid #1d1d28; }
  .sa-tab { background: transparent; border: none; border-bottom: 2px solid transparent; color: #9aa0a6; font-family: 'Geist Mono', ui-monospace, monospace; font-size: 10.5px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; padding: 9px 12px; cursor: pointer; }
  .sa-tab:hover { color: #cfd6da; }
  .sa-tab.active { color: #67e8f9; border-bottom-color: #67e8f9; }

  .sa-sec { display: none; }
  .sa-sec.active { display: block; }

  .sa-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 312px minmax(0,1fr); gap: 18px; }
  @media (max-width: 820px) { .sa-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }

  .sa-panel { background: #11131a; border: 1px solid #2a2a35; border-radius: 12px; padding: 16px; margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .sa-panel h3 { font-family: 'Geist Mono', ui-monospace, monospace; font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 0.16em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #67e8f9; font-weight: 700; margin: 0 0 12px; }

  .sa-ctl { display: grid; gap: 5px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .sa-ctl label { font-family: 'Geist Mono', ui-monospace, monospace; font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 0.06em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #9aa6b6; font-weight: 700; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; }
  .sa-ctl label span { color: #67e8f9; }
  .sa-ctl input[type=range] { width: 100%; accent-color: #67e8f9; }
  .sa-ctl select { width: 100%; background: #0a0a0c; border: 1px solid #2a2a35; color: #fff; padding: 7px 10px; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 12px; font-family: inherit; }

  .sa-seg { display: flex; gap: 6px; margin-bottom: 12px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .sa-seg button { flex: 1 1 auto; background: #0a0a0c; border: 1px solid #2a2a35; color: #9aa0a6; font-family: 'Geist Mono', ui-monospace, monospace; font-size: 10px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.05em; text-transform: uppercase; padding: 8px 6px; border-radius: 5px; cursor: pointer; }
  .sa-seg button.on { background: rgba(103,232,249,0.12); border-color: #67e8f9; color: #67e8f9; }

  .sa-metric { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr auto; gap: 8px; font-family: 'Geist Mono', ui-monospace, monospace; font-size: 11.5px; padding: 5px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid #1a1a25; }
  .sa-metric:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .sa-metric-l { color: #9aa6b6; }
  .sa-metric-v { color: #67e8f9; font-weight: 700; text-align: right; }
  .sa-metric-v.amber { color: #fbbf24; }
  .sa-metric-v.green { color: #86efac; }
  .sa-metric-v.red { color: #fca5a5; }
  .sa-metric-v.purple { color: #a78bfa; }

  .sa-svg { width: 100%; background: #0a0a0c; border: 1px solid #2a2a35; border-radius: 10px; display: block; }
  .sa-formula { font-family: 'Geist Mono', ui-monospace, monospace; font-size: 12px; color: #cfd6da; line-height: 1.7; background: #0a0a0c; border: 1px solid #1d1d28; border-radius: 8px; padding: 12px 14px; margin-top: 4px; }
  .sa-formula b { color: #fbbf24; }
  .sa-note { font-family: 'Geist Mono', ui-monospace, monospace; font-size: 10px; color: #6b7280; line-height: 1.6; margin-top: 8px; }
  .sa-plots { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 14px; }
  @media (max-width: 720px) { .sa-plots { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }

  .sa-legend { display: flex; gap: 16px; flex-wrap: wrap; font-family: 'Geist Mono', ui-monospace, monospace; font-size: 10px; color: #9aa6b6; margin-top: 8px; }
  .sa-legend span { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 5px; }
  .sa-legend i { width: 14px; height: 3px; border-radius: 2px; display: inline-block; }

  .sa-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-family: 'Geist Mono', ui-monospace, monospace; font-size: 11px; }
  .sa-table th { color: #fbbf24; text-align: left; font-weight: 700; padding: 5px 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #2a2a35; letter-spacing: 0.04em; }
  .sa-table td { color: #cfd6da; padding: 4px 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #161620; }
  .sa-table td.t { color: #fca5a5; font-weight: 700; }
  .sa-table td.c { color: #86efac; font-weight: 700; }
  .sa-table td.z { color: #6b7280; }

  /* text-content sections */
  .sa-prose { background: #11131a; border: 1px solid #2a2a35; border-radius: 12px; padding: 20px 22px; max-width: 900px; }
  .sa-prose p { color: #c5cbd2; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.65; margin: 0 0 14px; }
  .sa-prose ol { color: #c5cbd2; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; padding-left: 22px; margin: 0; }
  .sa-prose ol li { margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .sa-prose .eqs { font-family: 'Geist Mono', ui-monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.5px; color: #67e8f9; line-height: 1.9; background: #0a0a0c; border: 1px solid #1d1d28; border-radius: 8px; padding: 14px 16px; margin: 4px 0 16px; }
  .sa-prose .eqs b { color: #fbbf24; }
  .sa-prose .refs { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; }
  .sa-prose .refs li { font-size: 12.5px; color: #9aa6b6; line-height: 1.55; padding: 7px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid #1a1a25; font-family: 'Geist Mono', ui-monospace, monospace; }
  .sa-prose .refs li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

  /* self-assessment */
  .sa-quiz { max-width: 860px; }
  .sa-q { background: #11131a; border: 1px solid #2a2a35; border-radius: 12px; padding: 16px 18px; margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .sa-q .qhead { font-size: 14px; color: #fff; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 12px; line-height: 1.5; }
  .sa-q .qhead .qn { font-family: 'Geist Mono', ui-monospace, monospace; color: #fbbf24; font-size: 12px; margin-right: 8px; }
  .sa-opt { display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 9px; padding: 9px 11px; border: 1px solid #242430; border-radius: 8px; margin-bottom: 7px; cursor: pointer; font-size: 13px; color: #c5cbd2; }
  .sa-opt:hover { border-color: #3a3a45; background: #15171f; }
  .sa-opt input { accent-color: #67e8f9; margin-top: 2px; }
  .sa-opt.correct { border-color: #86efac; background: rgba(134,239,172,0.10); color: #d6f5e0; }
  .sa-opt.wrong { border-color: #fca5a5; background: rgba(252,165,165,0.08); color: #f5d6d6; }
  .sa-expl { font-family: 'Geist Mono', ui-monospace, monospace; font-size: 11px; line-height: 1.55; margin-top: 8px; padding: 9px 11px; border-radius: 7px; display: none; }
  .sa-expl.show { display: block; }
  .sa-expl.ok { color: #86efac; background: rgba(134,239,172,0.07); border: 1px solid rgba(134,239,172,0.2); }
  .sa-expl.no { color: #fca5a5; background: rgba(252,165,165,0.07); border: 1px solid rgba(252,165,165,0.2); }
  .sa-check { background: #67e8f9; color: #06222a; border: none; border-radius: 7px; padding: 9px 18px; font-family: 'Geist Mono', ui-monospace, monospace; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.06em; text-transform: uppercase; cursor: pointer; margin-top: 4px; }
  .sa-check:hover { background: #97f2ff; }
  .sa-score { font-family: 'Geist Mono', ui-monospace, monospace; font-size: 12px; color: #fbbf24; margin-left: 14px; font-weight: 700; }
</style>

<main class="sa-wrap">
  <a href="/aquintutor/labs" class="sa-back">
    <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" fill="none"><path d="M19 12H5M12 19l-7-7 7-7"/></svg>
    Back to Labs
  </a>
  <div class="sa-eye">Lab · Structural Analysis</div>
  <h1 class="sa-title">Trusses, beams &amp; <em>columns</em>, solved from first principles.</h1>
  <p class="sa-sub">Six working benches in the IIT Virtual Labs format. Pick an experiment, read its aim, theory and procedure, then drive the live simulation — every slider re-solves the underlying structural equations (joint equilibrium, double integration, influence lines, Euler buckling) — and test yourself with the self-assessment.</p>

  <div class="sa-shell">
    <aside class="sa-exp-list" id="expList">
      <h4>Experiments</h4>
      <button class="sa-exp active" data-exp="joints"><span class="num">1</span><span class="nm">Plane truss — method of joints</span></button>
      <button class="sa-exp" data-exp="sections"><span class="num">2</span><span class="nm">Plane truss — method of sections</span></button>
      <button class="sa-exp" data-exp="sfbm"><span class="num">3</span><span class="nm">Shear-force &amp; bending-moment diagrams</span></button>
      <button class="sa-exp" data-exp="defl"><span class="num">4</span><span class="nm">Beam deflection — Macaulay's method</span></button>
      <button class="sa-exp" data-exp="infl"><span class="num">5</span><span class="nm">Influence lines for a beam</span></button>
      <button class="sa-exp" data-exp="buck"><span class="num">6</span><span class="nm">Euler column buckling</span></button>
    </aside>

    <div class="sa-bench">

      <!-- ================= EXPERIMENT 1: METHOD OF JOINTS ================= -->
      <section class="sa-experiment active" data-exp="joints">
        <h2 class="sa-exp-head">Plane truss — method of joints</h2>
        <div class="sa-exp-tag">Experiment 1 · Joint equilibrium</div>
        <div class="sa-tabs">
          <button class="sa-tab active" data-sec="sim">Simulation</button>
          <button class="sa-tab" data-sec="aim">Aim</button>
          <button class="sa-tab" data-sec="theory">Theory</button>
          <button class="sa-tab" data-sec="proc">Procedure</button>
          <button class="sa-tab" data-sec="quiz">Self-assessment</button>
          <button class="sa-tab" data-sec="ref">References</button>
        </div>

        <div class="sa-sec active" data-sec="sim">
          <div class="sa-grid">
            <aside>
              <div class="sa-panel">
                <h3>Truss configuration</h3>
                <div class="sa-seg" id="j_truss">
                  <button class="on" data-t="howe">Howe (7 mbr)</button>
                  <button data-t="pratt">Pratt (7 mbr)</button>
                  <button data-t="warren">Warren (9 mbr)</button>
                  <button data-t="king">King post</button>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="sa-panel">
                <h3>Geometry &amp; loads</h3>
                <div class="sa-ctl"><label>Span L (m) <span id="j_LV">12.0</span></label><input id="j_L" type="range" min="6" max="24" step="0.5" value="12"/></div>
                <div class="sa-ctl"><label>Height h (m) <span id="j_hV">4.0</span></label><input id="j_h" type="range" min="1.5" max="9" step="0.5" value="4"/></div>
                <div class="sa-ctl"><label>Load P1 (kN) at panel 1 <span id="j_P1V">30</span></label><input id="j_P1" type="range" min="0" max="120" step="5" value="30"/></div>
                <div class="sa-ctl"><label>Load P2 (kN) at panel 2 <span id="j_P2V">40</span></label><input id="j_P2" type="range" min="0" max="120" step="5" value="40"/></div>
                <div class="sa-ctl"><label>Load P3 (kN) at panel 3 <span id="j_P3V">30</span></label><input id="j_P3" type="range" min="0" max="120" step="5" value="30"/></div>
              </div>
              <div class="sa-panel">
                <h3>Reactions &amp; checks</h3>
                <div class="sa-metric"><span class="sa-metric-l">Members m</span><span class="sa-metric-v" id="j_m">—</span></div>
                <div class="sa-metric"><span class="sa-metric-l">Joints j</span><span class="sa-metric-v" id="j_j">—</span></div>
                <div class="sa-metric"><span class="sa-metric-l">m + r vs 2j</span><span class="sa-metric-v" id="j_det">—</span></div>
                <div class="sa-metric"><span class="sa-metric-l">Reaction R_A (left pin)</span><span class="sa-metric-v" id="j_RA">—</span></div>
                <div class="sa-metric"><span class="sa-metric-l">Reaction R_B (right roller)</span><span class="sa-metric-v" id="j_RB">—</span></div>
                <div class="sa-metric"><span class="sa-metric-l">Max tension</span><span class="sa-metric-v red" id="j_Tmax">—</span></div>
                <div class="sa-metric"><span class="sa-metric-l">Max compression</span><span class="sa-metric-v green" id="j_Cmax">—</span></div>
                <div class="sa-metric"><span class="sa-metric-l">Equilibrium residual</span><span class="sa-metric-v purple" id="j_res">—</span></div>
              </div>
            </aside>
            <div>
              <div class="sa-panel">
                <h3>Truss diagram · member forces (kN)</h3>
                <svg id="j_view" class="sa-svg" viewBox="0 0 760 360" preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid meet"></svg>
                <div class="sa-legend">
                  <span><i style="background:#fca5a5"></i> Tension (+)</span>
                  <span><i style="background:#86efac"></i> Compression (-)</span>
                  <span><i style="background:#3a3a45"></i> Zero-force</span>
                </div>
                <div class="sa-note">Each joint is solved in turn from a joint with at most two unknowns; Sum Fx = 0 and Sum Fy = 0 give the member forces. Positive = tension (member pulls the joint).</div>
              </div>
              <div class="sa-panel">
                <h3>Member force table</h3>
                <table class="sa-table"><thead><tr><th>Member</th><th>Force (kN)</th><th>State</th><th>cos / sin</th></tr></thead><tbody id="j_tbody"></tbody></table>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="sa-sec" data-sec="aim"><div class="sa-prose"><p>To determine the axial force in every member of a statically-determinate plane truss using the method of joints, classify each member as in tension or compression, identify zero-force members, and verify the result against overall equilibrium.</p></div></div>

        <div class="sa-sec" data-sec="theory"><div class="sa-prose">
          <p>A pin-jointed plane truss carries load only as axial force in its members. At every frictionless pin the forces are concurrent, so the two scalar equilibrium equations Sum Fx = 0 and Sum Fy = 0 hold. The method of joints works through the truss one joint at a time, always choosing a joint with no more than two unknown member forces so the two equations can be solved directly. A member force assumed to pull the joint that comes out positive is in tension; a negative value is compression. The structure is statically determinate when m + r = 2j, where m is the number of members, r the number of reaction components and j the number of joints.</p>
          <div class="eqs">
            At each joint:&nbsp; <b>Sum Fx = 0,&nbsp; Sum Fy = 0</b><br/>
            For member k at angle theta:&nbsp; Fx contribution = F_k&middot;cos(theta),&nbsp; Fy = F_k&middot;sin(theta)<br/>
            Determinacy:&nbsp; <b>m + r = 2j</b>&nbsp; (r = 3 for one pin + one roller)<br/>
            Sign convention:&nbsp; F &gt; 0 tension, F &lt; 0 compression
          </div>
          <p>Reactions come first from global equilibrium of the whole truss: Sum M about one support gives the other reaction, then Sum Fy gives the first. With reactions known, the joints are solved in a sequence each exposing only two new unknowns.</p>
        </div></div>

        <div class="sa-sec" data-sec="proc"><div class="sa-prose"><ol>
          <li>Choose a truss configuration (Howe, Pratt, Warren or king-post).</li>
          <li>Set the span L and height h, then the joint loads P1, P2, P3 on the bottom chord.</li>
          <li>Read the support reactions R_A and R_B computed from global equilibrium.</li>
          <li>Inspect the coloured diagram: red members are in tension, green in compression, grey are zero-force.</li>
          <li>Read each member force in the table and confirm the equilibrium residual is essentially zero.</li>
          <li>Vary the height h and watch the inclined (web/rafter) forces fall as the truss is made deeper.</li>
        </ol></div></div>

        <div class="sa-sec" data-sec="quiz"><div class="sa-quiz" data-quiz="joints"></div></div>

        <div class="sa-sec" data-sec="ref"><div class="sa-prose"><ul class="refs">
          <li>R. C. Hibbeler, Structural Analysis, 10th ed., Pearson, Ch. 3 (Trusses).</li>
          <li>A. Kassimali, Structural Analysis, 6th ed., Cengage, Ch. 4.</li>
          <li>IIT Virtual Labs — Structural Analysis, vlabs.ac.in.</li>
        </ul></div></div>
      </section>

      <!-- ================= EXPERIMENT 2: METHOD OF SECTIONS ================= -->
      <section class="sa-experiment" data-exp="sections">
        <h2 class="sa-exp-head">Plane truss — method of sections</h2>
        <div class="sa-exp-tag">Experiment 2 · Cut &amp; equilibrate</div>
        <div class="sa-tabs">
          <button class="sa-tab active" data-sec="sim">Simulation</button>
          <button class="sa-tab" data-sec="aim">Aim</button>
          <button class="sa-tab" data-sec="theory">Theory</button>
          <button class="sa-tab" data-sec="proc">Procedure</button>
          <button class="sa-tab" data-sec="quiz">Self-assessment</button>
          <button class="sa-tab" data-sec="ref">References</button>
        </div>

        <div class="sa-sec active" data-sec="sim">
          <div class="sa-grid">
            <aside>
              <div class="sa-panel">
                <h3>Geometry &amp; loads</h3>
                <div class="sa-ctl"><label>Span L (m) <span id="x_LV">16.0</span></label><input id="x_L" type="range" min="8" max="24" step="0.5" value="16"/></div>
                <div class="sa-ctl"><label>Height h (m) <span id="x_hV">4.0</span></label><input id="x_h" type="range" min="1.5" max="8" step="0.5" value="4"/></div>
                <div class="sa-ctl"><label>Panel load P (kN) <span id="x_PV">40</span></label><input id="x_P" type="range" min="0" max="120" step="5" value="40"/></div>
              </div>
              <div class="sa-panel">
                <h3>Section cut</h3>
                <div class="sa-ctl"><label>Cut after panel n <span id="x_cutV">2</span></label><input id="x_cut" type="range" min="1" max="3" step="1" value="2"/></div>
                <div class="sa-seg" id="x_solve">
                  <button class="on" data-t="top">Solve top chord</button>
                  <button data-t="bot">Solve bottom chord</button>
                  <button data-t="diag">Solve diagonal</button>
                </div>
                <div class="sa-note">A Warren truss with 4 equal bottom panels; the section cuts three members so each unknown is found from one equation.</div>
              </div>
              <div class="sa-panel">
                <h3>Direct solution</h3>
                <div class="sa-metric"><span class="sa-metric-l">Reaction R_A</span><span class="sa-metric-v" id="x_RA">—</span></div>
                <div class="sa-metric"><span class="sa-metric-l">Reaction R_B</span><span class="sa-metric-v" id="x_RB">—</span></div>
                <div class="sa-metric"><span class="sa-metric-l">Chosen member</span><span class="sa-metric-v amber" id="x_mem">—</span></div>
                <div class="sa-metric"><span class="sa-metric-l">Moment arm / lever</span><span class="sa-metric-v" id="x_arm">—</span></div>
                <div class="sa-metric"><span class="sa-metric-l">Member force</span><span class="sa-metric-v" id="x_F">—</span></div>
                <div class="sa-metric"><span class="sa-metric-l">State</span><span class="sa-metric-v" id="x_state">—</span></div>
                <div class="sa-metric"><span class="sa-metric-l">Check vs joints solver</span><span class="sa-metric-v green" id="x_chk">—</span></div>
              </div>
            </aside>
            <div>
              <div class="sa-panel">
                <h3>Sectioned truss · free body to the left of the cut</h3>
                <svg id="x_view" class="sa-svg" viewBox="0 0 760 340" preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid meet"></svg>
                <div class="sa-note">The dashed line is the section. Members crossing it are exposed as the unknowns. Taking moments about the point where the other two intersect isolates the member you chose.</div>
              </div>
              <div class="sa-panel">
                <h3>Working</h3>
                <div class="sa-formula" id="x_work">—</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="sa-sec" data-sec="aim"><div class="sa-prose"><p>To determine the axial force in a single chosen truss member directly, without solving every joint, by passing an imaginary section through the truss and applying the three equations of equilibrium to one of the resulting free bodies.</p></div></div>

        <div class="sa-sec" data-sec="theory"><div class="sa-prose">
          <p>The method of sections cuts the truss along a line that crosses no more than three members whose forces are unknown. One portion of the truss is treated as a rigid free body in equilibrium under the external loads, the support reaction on that portion, and the three cut-member forces. Because a free body has three equations available — Sum Fx = 0, Sum Fy = 0 and Sum M = 0 — the three unknowns can be found, often each from a single well-chosen equation. To isolate one chord force, take moments about the point where the other two cut members intersect; their moment arms vanish and that chord force follows directly. A diagonal is best found from Sum Fy because the chords are usually horizontal.</p>
          <div class="eqs">
            On the free body:&nbsp; <b>Sum Fx = 0,&nbsp; Sum Fy = 0,&nbsp; Sum M = 0</b><br/>
            Top chord at depth h:&nbsp; <b>F_top = -M_cut / h</b>&nbsp; (moments about a bottom node)<br/>
            Bottom chord:&nbsp; <b>F_bot = +M_cut / h</b>&nbsp; (moments about a top node)<br/>
            Diagonal at angle alpha:&nbsp; <b>F_diag = V_cut / sin(alpha)</b>
          </div>
          <p>Here M_cut and V_cut are the bending moment and shear of the equivalent beam carried by the truss at the section. The method is fast because it never requires solving the joints upstream of the cut.</p>
        </div></div>

        <div class="sa-sec" data-sec="proc"><div class="sa-prose"><ol>
          <li>Set the span L, height h and the equal panel load P.</li>
          <li>Choose where to cut the truss with the panel slider.</li>
          <li>Select whether to solve the top chord, bottom chord or diagonal crossing the cut.</li>
          <li>Read the moment arm or lever used and the resulting member force.</li>
          <li>Compare the sectioned result with the full joints solver — they must agree.</li>
          <li>Move the cut and change the target member; note how the working changes equation but not principle.</li>
        </ol></div></div>

        <div class="sa-sec" data-sec="quiz"><div class="sa-quiz" data-quiz="sections"></div></div>

        <div class="sa-sec" data-sec="ref"><div class="sa-prose"><ul class="refs">
          <li>R. C. Hibbeler, Structural Analysis, 10th ed., Pearson, Sec. 3.5 (Method of Sections).</li>
          <li>R. C. Coates, M. G. Coutie, F. K. Kong, Structural Analysis, 3rd ed., Chapman &amp; Hall.</li>
          <li>IIT Virtual Labs — Structural Analysis, vlabs.ac.in.</li>
        </ul></div></div>
      </section>

